        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 28 at 3:05PM MDT until July 28 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 13 miles east of East Helena to near Montana City,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

Locations impacted include...
Goose Bay and Winston.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
